# {{PROJECT_NAME}} - Copilot instructions

Repository-wide instructions for GitHub Copilot. Keep changes small and reviewable. The full
guidance lives in [`docs/`](../docs/); the same rules drive [`CLAUDE.md`](../CLAUDE.md) and
[`AGENTS.md`](../AGENTS.md).

## Always

- Commit after every small fix or task: one logical change per commit, following
  [Conventional Commits](../CONTRIBUTING.md) with an imperative summary. Small commits beat big
  ones.
{{#TWO_BRANCH}}
- Two long-lived branches: feature work integrates on `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`; `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` is
  promoted to the always-deployable `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` via a periodic release PR. Never merge a
  feature branch straight into `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`.
- One directory per branch: never commit directly to `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` or `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`.
  Create each task's branch as its own worktree with `{{WT_CMD}} new <type>/<slug>`, which
  branches off `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`. Clean up merged worktrees with `{{WT_CMD}} gc`.
- Task lifecycle for "do task X from the backlog": fetch, create the worktree (off
  `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`), work in small commits, run the quality gate, push, open a PR into
  `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` (referencing the task), then hand it off for review. Never self-merge.
{{/TWO_BRANCH}}
{{#SINGLE_BRANCH}}
- One long-lived branch (trunk): feature work integrates directly on the always-deployable
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. There is no separate integration branch and no release PR; a feature branch
  merges into `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` once it is green.
- One directory per branch: never commit directly to `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. Create each task's
  branch as its own worktree with `{{WT_CMD}} new <type>/<slug>`, which branches off
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. Clean up merged worktrees with `{{WT_CMD}} gc`.
- Task lifecycle for "do task X from the backlog": fetch, create the worktree (off
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`), work in small commits, run the quality gate, push, open a PR into
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` (referencing the task), then hand it off for review. Never self-merge.
{{/SINGLE_BRANCH}}
- Run `git fetch` at the start of a session and before creating a new branch.
- Write English in code, comments, docs, and commits. {{COPY_LANGUAGE_NOTE}}
- No emojis and no fancy dashes anywhere; use the regular hyphen `-` only.
- Update docs and `CHANGELOG.md` in the same PR as the code they describe.

